How do I choose a laptop processor?How do I choose a laptop processor?
When choosing a laptop processor, pay attention to the number of cores, which allows software to run more efficiently. Additionally, higher-end processors typically support multi-threading and virtualization. All of these features work together to provide the fastest possible processor for your laptop.
read more
Can a laptop have both SSD and HDD?Can a laptop have both SSD and HDD?
Laptops can hold both a solid-state drive (SSD) and a hard disc drive (HDD), though the compact nature of laptops can make it challenging to fit both. Most modern laptops come equipped with just an SSD.
read more
Can you install more RAM on a laptop?Can you install more RAM on a laptop?
It's possible to install more RAM on a laptop, but the amount you can fit is determined by your laptop's motherboard. Most motherboards come with two or three RAM slots and use two strips of RAM in separate slots. You can remove and replace those strips with ones that have more memory.
read more
